  "title": "Customer Service Executive (Tuas) (5days) (Meals provided)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Highlight:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>5 days work week</li>\n  <li>Meals provided (Breakfast and lunch)</li>\n  <li>Comission to be earned after confirmation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Provide introductory information about the company and its products and services to new customers</p>\n<p>· Respond to customer inquiries</p>\n<p>· Advise customers on products or services to best suit their specific requirements</p>\n<p>· Prepare quotations and follow up with customers for their acceptance.</p>\n<p>· Document customer interactions when necessary, compiling job related documents to ensure that customer requirements are met.</p>\n<p>· Prepare delivery orders and other relevant documents.</p>\n<p>· Communicate all necessary job requirements clearly and efficiently to other stakeholders to ensure that customers’ requirements/instructions are addressed.</p>\n<p>· Resolve customers’ concerns, if any.</p>\n<p>· Build and maintain long term business relationship with new and existing customers</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Minimally 2 years of working experience, with experiences handling container shipment.</p>\n<p>· Prior customer service or sales coordinator experience will be an advantage</p>\n<p>· Preferably with knowledge for import and export shipments</p>\n<p>· Experience in logistics industry will be an advantage</p>\n<p>· Friendly and welcoming disposition</p>\n<p>· Has initiative, independent and able to work in dynamic environment</p>\n<p>· Good command of written and verbal English</p>\n<p>· Excellent organizational and multitasking skills</p>",
